Well catch up! Work for it a little right anything worth while ya gotta work for and this is just for myself to remember you got this! Anyone else in the same boat YOU GOT THIS! You want something go and get it, fight and work hard for it! I believe in you and so does Adriene and Benji

But yeah i closed my eyes cutting that lemon calm as ever. I trust you cant wait for the journey fr fr though theres something about your voice that really projects your life force energy and it's so comforting and reassuring so thank you for never stopping your channel I hope you never do at least. Youre awesome!!!

snippet.textDisplay:
Hi I've never done yoga... I've done pilates but never yoga. I finished chemo and radiation in July of 2019. I'm still recovering from all that my hair is growing but my body is in constant pain. I burned really bad and still have not fully recovered from that or from my mastectomy.
I'm hoping that yoga helps but I'm feeling defeated before even starting. My lower back hurts so much. I can't sit lay down or move to much without being in so much pain.
I'm planning on starting a healing journey with @yogawithadriene let's see how this goes! #breastcancer #stage2 #youngcancer #chemo #radiation #stillfighting

snippet.textDisplay: So I guess I'm a day late, I didn't know about this until a few minutes ago, sipping my coffee before the kids get up. In 2019 my family of five (one still in diapers) moved from the west coast to the east. It's "back home" for my husband and me but for our kids it's all new, especially for my oldest who had to face second grade in a completely unfamiliar school. We bought our new house in August and I love it but we're still working on making it "home" and probably still will be for a while. We just took down our first Christmas tree from this house and I am looking forward to a new year of breathing life and love into these spaces. I couldn't imagine a better themed journey to get back into the daily practice that I had very much fallen away from in all this crazy. Thank you for the gentle welcome back, Adrienne.

snippet.textDisplay:
Dear Adrienne,

I’ve now been practicing with you for about four years. That spans living in two different countries, three different “homes”, and such a vast spectrum and mental states. This year was bad for me. Bad for my sense of identity and self esteem. Bad for my sense of hope and trust in others. I had the worst job experience of my life that made me question my place in the world. This series being named Home couldn’t be more accurate. The only moments I have really felt home this year were when I could squeeze out a few minutes to hop on the mat with you. Those moments were too few, though, and my mind and body feel weary. Hoping this reset to home will help me find myself again buried under all the doubt, stress, fear, and struggle. I can’t thank you enough for what you mean to me and so many others. May your light shine on forever.
Love,
Alicia
